<body>
    <header>
        <h1>SASS Installation Guide</h1>
        <p>Step-by-step instructions to install and set up SASS for your projects</p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">üîÑ</span> Installation via NVM (Linux)</h3>
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">1</span>
                <strong>Install Node Version Manager (NVM)</strong>
                <pre>curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash</pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">2</span>
                <strong>Restart your terminal</strong>
                <pre>exit</pre>
                <p>Then reopen your terminal application.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">3</span>
                <strong>Install Node.js</strong>
                <pre>nvm install 20.16.0</pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">4</span>
                <strong>Use the installed Node version</strong>
                <pre>nvm use 20.16.0</pre>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">üì¶</span> Install SASS</h3>
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">1</span>
                <strong>Install SASS globally using npm</strong>
                <pre>npm install -g sass</pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">2</span>
                <strong>Verify installation</strong>
                <pre>sass --version</pre>
                <p>This should display the installed version of SASS.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
                <span class="step-number">3</span>
                <strong>Alternative: Install specific version (if needed)</strong>
                <pre>npm install -g sass@1.58.3</pre>
                <p>Replace "1.58.3" with your desired version.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Verification Steps</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>After installation, verify everything is working correctly:</p>
        <pre>
# Check Node.js version
node --version

# Check npm version
npm --version

# Check SASS version
sass --version
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Using SASS in Your Project</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">1</span>
            <strong>Navigate to your project directory</strong>
            <pre>cd /path/to/your/project</pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">2</span>
            <strong>Initialize package.json (if needed)</strong>
            <pre>npm init -y</pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">3</span>
            <strong>Compile SASS to CSS</strong>
            <pre>sass input.scss output.css</pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">4</span>
            <strong>Watch for changes during development</strong>
            <pre>sass --watch input.scss:output.css</pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="notes">
        <h3>üìù Notes</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>If you encounter permission errors on Linux/macOS, use <code>sudo</code> with npm commands or fix your npm permissions</li>
            <li>For Windows users, you can install Node.js directly from the official website if preferred</li>
            <li>The SASS package on npm is the primary implementation (Dart Sass)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="warning">
        <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Important</h3>
        <p>The version specification in the original instructions (<code>sass -v 3.7.4</code>) appears to be incorrect. The <code>-v</code> flag is for version checking, not installation. To install a specific version, use <code>npm install -g sass@3.7.4</code> but note that this version may not exist.</p>
    </div>
    
    <footer>
        <p>ALX Intermediate Frontend - 0x03-sass_scss</p>
        <p>Created as part of the installation guide project</p>
    </footer>
